{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A static prompt-template lint check rejects phase-specific instruction leakage copied from SKILL.md.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Failure boundary is the lint rule’s local matching logic: given template text plus leaked phase text, reject. The behavior is explicitly a \"static prompt-template lint check,\" so no module handoff, real OS/network/subprocess, or model output quality is required. Higher levels were rejected because the behavior text does not require assembled prompts, file loading, or LLM execution.","test_description":"Call the lint rule function with an in-memory template that includes a copied phase instruction snippet from SKILL.md and assert it returns a violation; call again with a clean template and assert no violation.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.84,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The fully assembled prompt produced by the real test harness (after interpolation/fixtures) still contains no phase-instruction leakage.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure appears at module boundaries (template + interpolation + fixture expansion + prompt assembly). Unit is too low because leakage can be introduced only after composition. Integration-brake: (a) no real network/subprocess/OS-only behavior is required; (b) no AI/ML quality dependence; (c) no multi-step agent chain. System/Agentic/Workflow are therefore disqualified by the behavior text \"fully assembled prompt ... after interpolation/fixtures.\"","test_description":"Run the real prompt builder pipeline with representative fixtures and interpolation variables, then assert the final assembled prompt string does not contain any forbidden phase-instruction fragments from SKILL.md.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The test invocation loads skill context from the plugin/skill files and validates behavior from that context rather than from hard-coded prompt rules.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This checks wiring across loader, file-backed skill context, and invocation config. A pure unit test could miss a hard-coded fallback path that only appears when modules are connected. Integration-brake: (a) requires local files but not real subprocess/network/OS event semantics; (b) does not require model judgment quality by itself; (c) no multi-step agent pipeline required by behavior text.","test_description":"Invoke the test harness with a real plugin/skill directory fixture and verify runtime prompt/context includes loaded SKILL.md content while a sentinel hard-coded rule is absent; fail if invocation succeeds without reading the skill file.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"If the relevant SKILL.md section is removed or degraded, the behavioral test fails with the same user-style prompt.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The stated oracle is behavioral failure under the same prompt when skill content regresses; that depends on real model behavior changing with context quality, which stubs can mask. System was considered but rejected: the key risk is not deterministic API contract handling, it is model-dependent behavioral quality. Workflow was rejected because only one model-evaluated behavior step is required by the text, not a multi-step chain.","test_description":"Run the same behavioral test prompt twice against the real model path: once with intact SKILL.md and once with the target section removed/degraded. Assert pass on intact context and fail on degraded context under identical test conditions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Raw model output is captured to a diagnostic artifact before any JSON parsing or extraction logic runs.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is an ordering/hand-off guarantee between invocation, artifact writer, and parser modules. Unit is too low if capture happens in one module and parsing in another. Integration-brake: (a) can be validated with local artifact writing, no real network/subprocess required; (b) does not depend on model quality, only pipeline order; (c) no multi-step agent chain.","test_description":"Execute one harness run with a deterministic stubbed model response and assert a raw-output artifact file is written and contains the unparsed text before parser/extractor is invoked (e.g., by instrumenting call order or using a parser that intentionally fails after artifact creation).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Assertions verify structured behavior (for example field placement or schema shape), not mere keyword presence that could come from prompt echoing.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The core failure boundary is assertion logic quality: distinguishing schema/placement checks from keyword contains checks. This can be caught with crafted local outputs (including prompt-echo text) without wiring full harness. Higher levels were rejected because behavior text focuses on assertion semantics, not OS/network/subprocess or model non-determinism.","test_description":"Test the assertion helper with two in-memory outputs: one that contains expected keywords but wrong schema/field placement (must fail), and one with correct structure (must pass). Ensure no keyword-only matcher is used as pass criterion.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":nu